The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in England so far as at 05 December is 1,464,803 (2,602.4 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 30 November, there were 85,022 new confirmed cases (151.1 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 23 November, there were 105,484 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 19% (20,462 fewer cases).
